Multiple sclerosis.

Nicholas R(1), Chataway J.

Author information:
(1)Imperial Healthcare Trust, London, UK.

INTRODUCTION: Multiple sclerosis is the most common cause of neurological 
disability in young adults. Irreversible disability can occur, but life 
expectancy is generally not affected.
METHODS AND OUTCOMES: We conducted a systematic review and aimed to answer the 
following clinical questions: What are the effects of interventions aimed at 
