Favourable cost-benefit in an early defibrillation programme using dual dispatch 
of ambulance and fire services in out-of-hospital cardiac arrest.

Sund B(1), Svensson L, Rosenqvist M, Hollenberg J.

Author information:
(1)Swedish Business School, Örebro University, 702 82, Örebro, Sweden. 
bjorn.sund@msb.se

AIMS: Out-of-hospital cardiac arrest is fatal without treatment, and time to 
defibrillation is an extremely important factor in relation to survival. We 
performed a cost-benefit analysis of dual dispatch defibrillation by ambulance 
